
[1]peril

   PER'IL, n. [L. periculum, from Gr. to try, to attempt, that is, to
   strain; an attempt, danger, hazard; to pass, to thrust in or transfix;
   L. experior; Eng. experience.]

   1. Danger; risk; hazard; jeopardy; particular exposure of person or
   property to injury,loss or destruction from any cause whatever.

   In perils of waters; in perils of robbers. 2 Cor.11.

   2. Danger denounced; particular exposure; You do it at your peril, or
   at the peril of your father's displeasure.

                  PER'IL, v.i. To be in danger. [Not used.]
